http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/MANUU-appointments-under-a-cloud/article13983174.ece

Maulana Azad Urdu National University (MANUU) initiated proceedings to replace a senior administrative functionary on Tuesday. The move is being seen as the university’s effort to correct appointment irregularities made by a previous Vice-Chancellor, which drew intense criticism in the past.The university had intimated its serving Chief Vigilance Officer (CVO) of the termination of official service. In its communication to the university Vice-Chancellor Dr. Mohammed Aslam Parvaiz, the UGC asked for three names of senior professors who could fill the vacancy.“The rules of UGC deemed the appointment irregular. The commission also sought to known why an appointment was made without consulting the commission and asked for three names of senior professors,” he said.